author: jmsnell
msg: WSDD supports the notion of Handler configuration parameters as being
"lockable".  That is, once the value is set, it cannot be changed.  This class
extends the standard java.util.Hashtable to support the notion of "lockable items".
"Locked" items cannot be overwritten with put() or deleted with remove()
